      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human review remains needed because the blocker is contributor-supplied real behavior proof, not a narrow automated code repair.; Cleared: The diff stays within MiniMax provider parsing/tests and does not change dependencies, workflows, package metadata, permissions, credentials, auth, or secret handling. (sha=62f542a0864f05acc86ede9f40c622f9bc9087ee)",
      "review_summary": "The PR wraps MiniMax music SSE frame JSON parsing in a try/catch to skip malformed frames and adds mocked plus local HTTP-server Vitest coverage.\n\nPR surface: Source +5, Tests +75. Total +80 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. by source inspection: current main routes non-empty MiniMax music SSE `data:` frames through a bare `JSON.parse`, so a malformed frame can throw before later valid audio is processed. I did not run a live malformed MiniMax stream in this read-only review.",
