      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(minimax): guard music generation SSE JSON.parse against malformed frames",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.ts:266` calls `JSON.parse(json)` on SSE data frames without try/catch. A malformed SSE data frame → unhandled `SyntaxError` → music generation crashes instead of skipping the bad frame.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(json)` in try/catch → `continue` (skip frame) on malformed SSE data\n- `extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.test.ts`: two tests verifying the fix:\n  1. Mocked SSE test: malformed frames skipped, valid audio decoded\n  2. **Real HTTP server test**: starts a local `node:http` server serving SSE stream with malformed frame + valid audio hex, calls `generateMusic()` against it through real HTTP transport\n\nLabel: bugfix | merge-risk: 🟢 minimal | AI-assisted\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP server proof (L2) — vitest + live node:http server\n\nThe test starts a real `node:http` server on `127.0.0.1:0`, serves an SSE stream with `data: NOT JSON {{{` followed by a valid MiniMax audio frame, then calls `generateMusic()` via `postJsonRequest` forwarded to the local server through real `fetch()`.\n\n```\n$ MINIMAX_API_KEY=test pnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.test.ts\n\n ✓ real HTTP server proof: malformed SSE frame → skip, valid audio → decoded\n ✓ skips malformed SSE data frames and processes valid audio frames\n ... (all existing tests pass)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  15 passed (15)\n   Duration  48.70s\n```\n\nNo mock `new Response()` — the SSE bytes travel over a real TCP socket through Node.js `fetch()`, then through the actual `readStreamingTrack` try/catch path.",
